column2: Confucianism is an ethical and philosophical religion founded by Confucius, centered on humanism, awareness, family, and good service. After Confucius' death the religion would gain more metaphysical and supernatural components.

Taoism, coming from the word Tao meaning "Way", is a religion centered on living in the balance and harmony with The Tao. Highly dualistic, Taoism includes two conflicting forces known as Yin and Yang.
